icy, new SIMD/SWAR backends should have a proptest oracle proving equivalence with the scalar path. Existing proptests (`row_json_produces_valid_json`, `row_json_paths_agree`) exercise this indirectly through JSON serialization, but there is no direct `first_escape_pos` oracle test comparing SWAR output to the original scalar loop. |\n| ADVISORY | `dev-docs/verification/kani-boundary-contract.toml` | `crates/ffwd-output/src/row_json.rs` now contains a non-trivial SWAR byte scanning primitive and could be a candidate for `recommended` status in the boundary contract, especially given the bit-manipulation complexity of the control-char / quote / backslash detection logic. |","text":"> [!NOTE]\n> Your check run agent prompt is: [`.macroscope/check-run-agents/verification-coverage.md`](https://github.com/strawgate/fastforward/blob/main/.macroscope/check-run-agents/verification-coverage.md)\n> More information about how Check Run Agents work can be found in our [Help Center](https://docs.macroscope.com/check-run-agents).\n\n### Files examined\n\n- `crates/ffwd-output/src/row_json.rs` (PR head) \u2014 verified no `#[cfg(kani)]` blocks exist; confirmed existing proptest suite covers `write_json_string` indirectly\n- `crates/ffwd-output/src/lib.rs` \u2014 confirmed 8 Kani proofs present (unchanged), only re-export line added\n- `crates/ffwd-output/src/json_lines.rs` \u2014 sink wiring change to use `write_batch_json_resolved`\n- `crates/ffwd-output/src/stdout.rs` \u2014 stdout sink wiring change to use `write_batch_json_resolved`\n- `dev-docs/VERIFICATION.md` \u2014 read verification policy and per-module status table\n- `dev-docs/verification/kani-boundary-contract.toml` \u2014 confirmed `row_json.rs` is not tracked\n- `dev-docs/CRATE_RULES.md` \u2014 confirmed ffwd-output has boundary contract tracking obligation\n- `dev-docs/CHANGE_MAP.md` \u2014 checked verification-impacting change triggers\n\n### Why no blocking issues\n\n1. `row_json.rs` has no existing verification obligations (not in boundary contract, not in ffwd-core).\n2. The new `write_batch_json_resolved` public function is a thin loop wrapper \u2014 it delegates entirely to the already-tested `write_row_json_resolved`.\n3. The SWAR optimization is indirectly covered by existing proptests that validate all JSON output is parseable and paths agree between `write_row_json` and `write_row_json_resolved`.\n4. No state machine or protocol changes \u2014 no TLA+ impact.","annotations_count":0,"annotations_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/strawgate/fastforward/check-runs/73332100379/annotations"},"check_suite":{"id":66478121847,"node_id":"CS_kwDORzg8fM8AAAAPemejdw","head_branch":"copilot/optimize-json-performance-benchmarks","head_sha":"5f51ffb89999e1f7232658f8c96175c10d0b0c9b","status":"queued","conclusion":null,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/strawgate/fastforward/check-suites/66478121847","before":"3ac3a34c9f75b3b131ea8cad14a99cd8ccf24bfc","after":"5f51ffb89999e1f7232658f8c96175c10d0b0c9b","pull_requests":[{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/strawgate/fastforward/pulls/2727","id":3594001429,"number":2727,"head":{"ref":"copilot/optimize-json-performance-benchmarks","sha":"5f51ffb89999e1f7232658f8c96175c10d0b0c9b","repo":{"id":1194867836,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/strawgate/fastforward","name":"fastforward"}},"base":{"ref":"main","sha":"4e66ffe253964dde54f3cbb980343cc351e33f79","repo":{"id":1194867836,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/strawgate/fastforward","name":"fastforward"}}}],"app":{"id":900172,"client_id":"Iv23liK7cN4LHJJrxDDB","slug":"macroscopeapp","node_id":"A_kwHOCEtgjs4ADbxM","owner":{"login":"prassoai","id":139157646,"node_id":"O_kgDOCEtgjg","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/139157646?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/prassoai","html_url":"https://github.com/prassoai","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/prassoai/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/prassoai/following{/other